  "answer": "The passage appears in the *Vṛhaspatitattva*, Chapter 1.[^1]\n\nThe honeycomb-and-young-bees image is quoted verbatim as follows: \"*Māyā* is like the honeycomb, and the *ātmā* is like the young bees. They are face-down, which means they are bent over; the *ātmā* looks only downward, unaware of the *tattva* above it.\"[^2]\n\n[^1]: *Vṛhaspatitattva*, Chapter 1, [chapter](/works/unknown-vrhaspatitattva-b60b28/01/translation/).\n[^2]: *Vṛhaspatitattva*, Chapter 1, [paragraph](/works/unknown-vrhaspatitattva-b60b28/01/translation/#p-643885).",
